      "text": "HTML Table Borders"
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "❮ Previous\nNext ❯"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "HTML tables can have borders of different styles and shapes."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "How To Add a Border"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To add a border, use the CSS border property on \ntable, th, and \ntd elements:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "css",
          "code": "table, th, td\n{\n  border: 1px solid black;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Collapsed Table Borders"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To avoid having double borders like in the example above, set the CSS border-collapse \nproperty to collapse."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This will make the borders collapse into a single border:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "css",
          "code": "table, th, td {  border: 1px solid black;\n   \n border-collapse: collapse;}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Style Table Borders"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you set a background color of each cell,\nand give the border a white color (the same as the document background),\nyou get the impression of an invisible border:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "css",
          "code": "table, th, td {  border: 1px solid white;\n   \n border-collapse: collapse;}th, td {  background-color: #96D4D4;\n  }"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Round Table Borders"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "With the border-radius property, the borders get rounded corners:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ],
        [
          "",
          "",
          ""
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "css",
          "code": "table, th, td {  border: 1px solid \n  black;\n   \n border-radius: 10px;}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Skip the border around the table by leaving out table from the css selector:"
